file.content:
This section specifies compositional requirements between motifs.
When a term voices a particular motif, these rules define what companion elements are required.

=== Operation Detail-Site Completeness

A term voiced
{axvo_procedure}
or
{axvo_method}
with a detail-site subdocument requires:

* {axhob_operation}
— opens the hierarchy block, with lookahead to the operation's linked term

* At least one
{axhos_step}
— what the operation does

* {axhoc_completion}
— how the operation signals success or failure

Optional markers that MAY be included:

* {axhopt_typed_parameter}
/{axhopa_arg_parameter}
/{axhopm_motif_parameter}
— input parameters (typed/arg variants use 1-arity lookahead; motif is bare)

* {axhoot_typed_output}
/{axhoom_motif_output}
— produced artifacts (typed variant uses 1-arity lookahead; motif is bare)

* {axhoq_precondition}
— environmental state requirements before execution

* {axhog_guarantee}
— environmental state guarantees after success

=== CLI Subcommand Completeness

Voicing as
{axi_cli_subcommand}
requires:

* Exit Status section voiced as
{axa_exit_uniform}
or
{axa_exit_enumerated}
(which voice
{axhoc_completion}
in CLI context)

* Arguments section voiced as
{axa_argument_list}
(which voices
{axhopt_typed_parameter}
/{axhopa_arg_parameter}
in CLI context; may list zero arguments if operation takes none)

=== CLI Option Completeness

Voicing as
{axa_cli_option}
requires the definition text to specify:

* Long form (e.g., `--file`)

* Short form or explicit absence (e.g., `-f` or "none")

* Default value, if the argument is used with
{axd_defaulted}

=== Argument List Item Qualification

Within an
{axa_argument_list},
each item requires a preceding
{axd_dimension}
annotation specifying at minimum:

* {axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* {axd_defaulted}
if a default value applies

=== Type Voicing Qualification

Voicing a type (subspecializing
{axt_*}
or
{axtu_*}
motifs) constrains dimension usage.

Valid dimensions:

* {axd_list}
— type intrinsically represents delimited collection

Invalid dimensions:

* {axd_required},
{axd_optional},
{axd_defaulted}
— presence applies to usage sites, not type definitions

* {axd_repeated}
— repetition applies to usage sites, not type definitions

=== Regime Specification Completeness

Voicing as
{axrg_regime}
requires:

* Format dimension (
{axf_bash},
{axf_makefile},
{axf_json},
etc.) specifying how assignments are carried

* Provenance dimension (
{axrd_file_sourced},
{axrd_env_inherited},
or
{axrd_constructed})
declaring how
{axrg_assignment_s}
arrive

=== Regime Variable Qualification

Voicing as
{axrg_variable}
requires:

* Type in annotation (base type motif or type voicing)

* At minimum
{axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* {axd_defaulted}
if a default value applies

Valid dimensions:

* {axd_required}
— variable must have assignment

* {axd_optional}
— variable may be absent

* {axd_defaulted}
— fallback value when absent

* {axd_list}
— inherited from type voicing; variable's type is a delimited collection

Invalid dimensions:

* {axd_repeated}
— regime files use unique keys; multiple assignments of same variable not permitted

* {axd_nullable}
— format-dependent;
{axf_bash}
has no null distinct from empty string

=== Regime Voicing Annotation Completeness

{axvr_regime}
requires:

* {axf_format}
dimension specifying how
{axrg_assignment_s}
are carried

{axvr_variable}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the parent regime

* {axd_required}
or
{axd_optional}

* Type
{axl_motif}
(base type or type voicing)

{axvr_group}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the parent regime

=== Regime Hierarchy Consistency

* {axvr_group}
with
{axd_conditional}
requires corresponding
{axhrgb_group}
in subdocument to have at least one
{axhrgc_gate}

* {axvr_group}
without
{axd_conditional}:
corresponding
{axhrgb_group}
must have no
{axhrgc_gate}

* Every
{axvr_variable}
under a regime should appear as either
{axhrv_variable}
or
{axhrgv_variable}
in the subdocument

=== Operation Voicing Annotation Completeness

{axvo_procedure}
requires:

* Exactly one lifecycle dimension:
{axd_transient},
{axd_longrunning},
or
{axd_periodic}

* If
{axd_grouped}:
second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be an
{axo_group}

{axvo_method}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the affiliated
{axo_entity}

* Exactly one lifecycle dimension:
{axd_transient},
{axd_longrunning},
or
{axd_periodic}

* If
{axd_grouped}:
third
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be an
{axo_group}

{axvo_group}
requires:

* Second
{mcm_attribute_reference}
in definition text must be the affiliated
{axo_entity}

* Optional exposure dimension:
{axd_tabtarget},
{axd_slash_command},
or other interface mechanism specifying the default exposure for external members

=== Operation Hierarchy Consistency

* {axhob_operation}
attribute reference must match a term voiced
{axvo_procedure},
{axvo_method},
or
{axvo_tabtarget}
at the
{axl_definition_site}

* Every
{axhoc_completion},
{axhopt_typed_parameter},
{axhopa_arg_parameter},
{axhopm_motif_parameter},
{axhoot_typed_output},
{axhoom_motif_output},
{axhoq_precondition},
{axhog_guarantee},
and
{axhos_step}
must appear within
{axhob_operation}
scope

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account_s}
in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all SAs, filters to director-prefixed accountIds, and emits one fact per discovered SA via
{buf_write_fact_multi}
against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` extension constant.
Fact content is empty (presence-as-fact); stdout assertion of individual identities is retired.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` from the resulting access token

//axhos_step
. *List service accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to director service accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, retain only entries whose `.accountId` begins with the `${RBCC_role_director}-` prefix
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNTS»` — the filtered set; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered {rbtr_director}*:
.. For each entry in `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNTS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` by stripping the `${RBCC_role_director}-` prefix from the entry's `accountId`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: composed as `<roster_subdir>/«IDENTITY»` (the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` (resolves at source time to `roster-director`)
.... `<value>`: `""` (empty content — presence-as-fact convention per RBS0:1081)

//axhos_step
. *Report count*:
.. {rbbc_show}
total count of emitted director fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution rosters {rbtr_director} service accounts via per-SA fact emission — one `roster-director` fact file per discovered identity.
The operation is read-only; no service accounts are created or modified.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`hallmarks/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SUBTREE»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/` where `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` derives from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled from `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `hallmarks`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARK_PACKAGES»` as the list of decoded package names whose prefix equals `«SUBTREE»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«ARK_PACKAGES»` is empty: "No packages found under «SUBTREE» — hallmark not present in registry"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. Unless `--force` flag provided:
... {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure «COUNT» packages under «SUBTREE»:" followed by each entry in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`
... {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
... {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Each Enumerated Package*:
.. For each `«PACKAGE»` in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ENCODED»` as `«PACKAGE»` with `/` replaced by `%2F`
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/delete[GAR REST API: packages.delete] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages/«ENCODED»`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response (deletion returns a long-running operation; the 200 is treated as accepted)
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete package «PACKAGE» (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Hallmark abjured: «INPUT_HALLMARK» («COUNT» packages)"
.. For each deleted package:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «PACKAGE» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree has been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.
Because enumeration drives the delete set, there is no separate existence check and no orphan-detection branch: whatever lives in the subtree is removed, and an empty subtree is itself the "not present" signal.
Deleting a package removes all of its tags in one call — per-basename HEAD/DELETE dances are no longer required.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_access_jwt_probe}

NOTE: This operation probes
{gar_service}
read access for a specified
{rbtr_role}
by performing a JWT-to-OAuth token exchange and then calling the Artifact Registry packages.list API.
It may repeat for a configured number of iterations with a configurable delay, enabling sustained access verification and token lifecycle testing.

The operation accepts a role parameter selecting among
{rbtr_governor},
{rbtr_director},
and
{rbtr_retriever},
each with Owner, repoAdmin, and reader permissions respectively.
All three roles have Artifact Registry read access, so a successful response confirms both token validity and role-specific permission.

//axhos_step
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_ROLE»` provided as first argument: one of `governor`, `director`, or `retriever`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if role missing: "Role parameter required (governor|director|retriever)"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if role unrecognized: "Unknown role: «INPUT_ROLE» — must be governor, director, or retriever"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ITERATION_COUNT»` from `--count` flag (default: 1)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DELAY_MS»` from `--delay_ms` flag (default: 0)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«ITERATION_COUNT»` is not a positive integer: "Count must be a positive integer"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«DELAY_MS»` is not a non-negative integer: "Delay must be a non-negative integer"

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Role Configuration*:
.. If `«INPUT_ROLE»` is `governor`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ROLE_DISPLAY»` as `Governor`
... {rbbc_store}
`«RBRA_FILE»` from
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}
.. If `«INPUT_ROLE»` is `director`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ROLE_DISPLAY»` as `Director`
... {rbbc_store}
`«RBRA_FILE»` from
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
.. If `«INPUT_ROLE»` is `retriever`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ROLE_DISPLAY»` as `Retriever`
... {rbbc_store}
`«RBRA_FILE»` from
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
.. {rbbc_require}
`«RBRA_FILE»` exists on the filesystem
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if file missing: "«ROLE_DISPLAY» RBRA file missing at «RBRA_FILE»"

//axhos_step
. *Construct Verification Endpoint*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VERIFY_URL»` as:
+
`https://artifactregistry.googleapis.com/v1/projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}/repositories/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/packages`

//axhos_step
. *Execute Probe Iterations*:
.. For each iteration `«I»` from 1 to `«ITERATION_COUNT»`:

... *Acquire «ROLE_DISPLAY» Token*:
.... Execute
{rbtoe_jwt_oauth_exchange}
with `«RBRA_FILE»`
.... {rbbc_store}
`«ROLE_TOKEN»` from exchange result
.... {rbbc_fatal}
if token exchange fails: "Iteration «I»: JWT-to-OAuth exchange failed for «ROLE_DISPLAY»"

... *Call Artifact Registry Packages API*:
.... {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[artifactregistry.projects.locations.repositories.packages.list] with:
..... method: `GET`
..... endpoint: `«VERIFY_URL»`
..... header: `Authorization: Bearer «ROLE_TOKEN»`
.... {rbbc_store}
`«HTTP_STATUS»` from response status code
.... {rbbc_store}
`«RESPONSE_BODY»` from response body

... *Evaluate Response*:
.... If `«HTTP_STATUS»` is 200:
..... {rbbc_show}
`Iteration «I»/«ITERATION_COUNT»: «ROLE_DISPLAY» OK — packages.list HTTP 200`
.... If `«HTTP_STATUS»` is 403:
..... {rbbc_fatal}
"Iteration «I»: «ROLE_DISPLAY» access denied — HTTP 403 (token valid but role lacks Artifact Registry read permission)"
.... If `«HTTP_STATUS»` is 401:
..... {rbbc_fatal}
"Iteration «I»: «ROLE_DISPLAY» token rejected — HTTP 401 (token exchange succeeded but token is invalid)"
.... If `«HTTP_STATUS»` is one of 500, 502, 503, or 504 (transient server-side error):
..... Re-execute the {rbbc_call} up to 3 total attempts, sleeping with exponential backoff between attempts (2s, then 4s)
..... On any non-5xx response within the retry window, re-enter *Evaluate Response* with that status
..... {rbbc_fatal}
if all 3 attempts return a 5xx status: "Iteration «I»: «ROLE_DISPLAY» repeated transient HTTP «HTTP_STATUS» after 3 attempts"
.... Otherwise:
..... {rbbc_fatal}
"Iteration «I»: «ROLE_DISPLAY» unexpected HTTP «HTTP_STATUS»: «RESPONSE_BODY»"

... *Apply Inter-Iteration Delay* (if not final iteration):
.... If `«DELAY_MS»` is greater than 0 and `«I»` is less than `«ITERATION_COUNT»`:
..... {rbbc_show}
`Sleeping «DELAY_MS»ms before next iteration`
..... Sleep `«DELAY_MS»` milliseconds

//axhos_step
. *Display Summary*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`«ROLE_DISPLAY» JWT access probe complete: «ITERATION_COUNT»/«ITERATION_COUNT» iterations passed`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when all iterations confirm that the selected role's JWT-derived OAuth token grants read access to the
{gar_service}
packages list endpoint.
Completion demonstrates both that JWT-to-OAuth token exchange is operational for the role and that the resulting token carries the expected Artifact Registry read permissions.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_vouch}

NOTE: This operation vouches for every *pending*
{rbtga_ark}
in
{rbtgi_repository},
where *pending* means a hallmark whose subtree contains both
{rbtga_ark_image}
and
{rbtga_ark_about}
basenames but no
{rbtga_ark_vouch}.
The
{rbtr_director}
enumerates the full hallmark corpus via a single GAR REST `packages.list` call (the same shared helper used by
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally}),
identifies pending hallmarks, resolves the vessel name from each hallmark's
{rbtga_ark_about}
metadata (since vessel identity no longer lives in the GAR path), and dispatches
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
per hallmark.
Mode-awareness (conjure, bind, graft) lives inside
{rbtgo_ark_vouch};
batch vouch does not branch on mode.

NOTE: *Fail-fast semantics.* If
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
fails for any hallmark, the batch terminates via fatal error at that hallmark.
There is no skip-with-warning path and no summary-count-masking of failures: a broken hallmark demands immediate attention, not quiet continuation.

The
{rbtr_director}
batch-vouches arks:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Hallmark Packages*:
.. {rbbc_call}
the shared hallmark enumeration helper — a single
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list]
call under `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/` (`RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT`), filtered to `<hallmark>/<basename>` shape
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PAIRS»` as sorted `<hallmark> <basename>` pairs (same shape produced for
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally})

//axhos_step
. *Identify Pending Hallmarks (Pass 1)*:
.. Iterate `«PAIRS»` in sort order; each contiguous run of the same hallmark is one
{rbtga_hallmark}'s
ark inventory.
.. For each hallmark, record whether
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
and
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
each appear in its run.
.. A hallmark is *pending* when `image` and `about` are present and `vouch` is absent.
Collect pending hallmarks into `«PENDING»` (in-memory sequence).
.. If `«PENDING»` is empty, the procedure completes successfully with no vouches submitted.

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Vessel and Vouch Per Pending Hallmark (Pass 2)*:
.. For each `«HALLMARK»` in `«PENDING»`:
... Extract the hallmark's
{rbtga_ark_about}
artifact (package `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«HALLMARK»/about`, tag `«HALLMARK»`) to a scratch directory via the shared GAR artifact extraction helper
... Read `.vessel_name` from the extracted `build_info.json` via `jq`
... {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_DIR»` as `«RBRR_VESSEL_DIR»/«VESSEL_NAME»`
... {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_DIR»` exists on disk — the vessel named in `about` metadata must correspond to a configured vessel in the current regime
... {rbbc_fatal}
if the `about` artifact cannot be extracted, `build_info.json` is missing, `.vessel_name` is empty, or `«VESSEL_DIR»` does not exist — the `about` artifact is the sole source of vessel identity for this batch; a gap there is a fail-fast stop
... Invoke
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
with `«VESSEL_DIR»` and `«HALLMARK»`.
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
loads the vessel's
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
internally and dispatches the appropriate verification (conjure: SLSA DSSE verification; bind: digest-pin; graft: GRAFTED stamp).
... {rbbc_fatal}
if
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
fails — the batch terminates at the broken hallmark.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
. *Display Summary*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Batch vouch complete — N/N hallmark(s) vouched` where N is the initial pending count

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates one
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
artifact per pending hallmark (N total, where N = initial pending count).
The batch runs sequentially; a failure at any hallmark halts the remainder.
+
*Scope of vessel resolution*: Reading `vessel_name` from `build_info.json` is a narrow anticipation of the broader vessel-from-metadata pattern (AAL territory) — applied locally inside batch vouch only, because
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
's signature still takes a vessel directory.
Other operations (tally, plumb, abjure) continue to not surface vessel.
+
*Two-pass shape*: Pass 1 collects pending hallmarks into memory before Pass 2 begins processing.
Each
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
invocation sources credentials and issues Cloud Build calls that would silently consume loop stdin if the pending set were streamed; the in-memory collection decouples enumeration from dispatch.
+
*Idempotency*: Re-running batch vouch after a successful batch finds an empty pending set (every prior pending hallmark now has `vouch` present) and exits with no action.
+
*No mode pre-check*: Earlier shapes of this operation pre-probed SLSA provenance for conjure-mode hallmarks to skip-with-warning those lacking provenance.
That pattern is gone — all mode-specific verification happens inside
{rbtgo_ark_vouch},
and any failure there surfaces as a fail-fast stop rather than being absorbed into a summary count.

Rosters
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account_s} in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission
({rbtgog_governor}).

