//axhob_operation
{bust_node_regime_list}

NOTE: Lists every {burn_regime} profile in the local station subtree
without contacting any remote node.
Read-only enumeration scoped to the current {burs_user}.

//axhoq_precondition
The station subtree at `.buk/users/{burs_user}/` exists and is readable
by the calling user.

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate local profiles*: scan the station subtree for {burn_regime}
profile files

//axhos_step
. *Display roster*: print each discovered {burn_alias} together with its
{burn_tier} classification

//axhog_guarantee
No remote network contact occurred and no profile file was modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 on successful enumeration; an empty roster is success.
Non-zero only when the station subtree cannot be read.

//axhob_operation
{bust_node_regime_render}

NOTE: Prints the resolved field set for a single {burn_regime} profile
identified by a positional {burn_alias} argument.
Read-only; no remote contact.

//axhoq_precondition
A {burn_regime} profile with the given {burn_alias} exists in the local
station subtree under the current {burs_user}.

//axhos_step
. *Locate profile*: resolve the profile file for the supplied
{burn_alias} under the station subtree

//axhos_step
. *Resolve fields*: parse the profile and emit every defined
{burn_regime} field assignment

//axhog_guarantee
No remote network contact occurred and no field was modified on disk.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 on successful render.
Non-zero when the {burn_alias} is not found or the profile fails to
parse.

//axhob_operation
{bust_node_regime_validate}

NOTE: Validates a single {burn_regime} profile, identified by positional
{burn_alias}, for required-field presence, valid {burn_tier}, and
key-file accessibility.
Read-only; no remote contact.

//axhoq_precondition
A {burn_regime} profile with the given {burn_alias} exists in the local
station subtree.

//axhos_step
. *Load profile*: parse the profile file for the supplied {burn_alias}

//axhos_step
. *Required fields*: confirm {burn_host}, {burn_user}, {burn_alias},
and {burn_tier} are present

//axhos_step
. *Tier sanity*: confirm {burn_tier} is exactly one of
`privileged | workload`

//axhos_step
. *Key reachable*: resolve {burn_key_file} and confirm the file is
readable by the calling user

//axhog_guarantee
The verdict reflects the on-disk state at call time; no field was
modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when every check passes.
Non-zero with a diagnostic message identifying the first failed check.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_cygwin}

NOTE: Establishes privileged BURN trust against a Cygwin node by writing
the privileged {burn_regime} profile and driving the Cygwin-specific
{busn_garrison} ceremony.
Idempotent on re-run.

//axhoq_precondition
The remote Windows account named in {burn_user} is a member of the
local Administrators group on the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
OpenSSH server is reachable on {burn_host} from the calling station,
and the operator can complete the console-side handshake at the
Windows keyboard (or RDP).

//axhos_step
. *Write profile*: persist the privileged {burn_regime} profile to the
station subtree with `{burn_tier} = privileged`

//axhos_step
. *Console handshake*: drive the Cygwin-specific console ceremony to
install the station pubkey into
`C:\ProgramData\ssh\administrators_authorized_keys`

//axhos_step
. *Probe trust*: confirm passwordless SSH to the privileged account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
The privileged {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally and the
station's {burn_ssh_pubkey} is trusted on the remote Cygwin node.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the trust handshake completes and the verification probe
succeeds.
Non-zero on profile-write failure, console-handshake refusal, or final
SSH probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_wsl}

NOTE: Establishes privileged BURN trust against a WSL node by writing
the privileged {burn_regime} profile and driving the WSL-specific
{busn_garrison} ceremony.
Idempotent on re-run.

//axhoq_precondition
The remote Windows account hosting the WSL distribution is a member of
the local Administrators group, and the WSL distribution named in
{burn_command} is registered for that account on the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
OpenSSH server is reachable on {burn_host} from the calling station,
and the operator can complete the console-side handshake at the
Windows keyboard (or RDP).

//axhos_step
. *Write profile*: persist the privileged {burn_regime} profile to the
station subtree with `{burn_tier} = privileged` and the WSL launcher
recorded in {burn_command}

//axhos_step
. *Console handshake*: drive the WSL-specific console ceremony — bash
owns control flow and PowerShell is the syscall layer — to install the
station pubkey into
`C:\ProgramData\ssh\administrators_authorized_keys`

//axhos_step
. *Probe trust*: confirm passwordless SSH to the privileged account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
The privileged {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally and the
station's {burn_ssh_pubkey} is trusted on the remote WSL node.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the trust handshake completes and the verification probe
succeeds.
Non-zero on profile-write failure, WSL launcher unavailability,
console-handshake refusal, or final SSH probe failure.

